title: Strange build error on vscode-remote terminal with multipass

labels.name: A-linkage
labels.description: Area: linking into static, shared libraries and binaries

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
I have a very strange build error. I can't judge whether it is a rust build problem or a vscode-remote problem or a multipass problem. I‘m working on a macOS Big Sur with intel core, then I have a ubuntu install with multipass on it, and then i build rust on the ubuntu. Then i use `multipass mount` command mount my code on ubuntu. If i use `multipass shell` or `ssh` login my ubuntu,then `cargo build` work fine, BUT if i use vscode-remote login my ubuntu,then use vscode terminal `cargo build` will link error. ld cannot find some rlibs. It seems these rlibs delay for read. if these rlibs cached with a success build first,all build works fine. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.50.0-nightly (1c389ffef 2020-11-24) binary: rustc commit-hash: 1c389ffeff814726dec325f0f2b0c99107df2673 commit-date: 2020-11-24 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.50.0-nightly ``` `ld --version`: ``` GNU ld (GNU Binutils for Ubuntu) 2.26.1 Copyright (C) 2015 Free Software Foundation, Inc. This program is free software; you may redistribute it under the terms of the GNU General Public License version 3 or (at your option) a later version. This program has absolutely no warranty. ``` `cc --version`: ``` cc (Ubuntu 5.4.0-6ubuntu1~16.04.12) 5.4.0 20160609 Copyright (C) 2015 Free Software Foundation, Inc. This is free software; see the source for copying conditions. There is NO warranty; not even for MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. ``` `multipass version`: ``` multipass 1.5.0+mac multipassd 1.5.0+mac ``` `lsb_release -a`: ``` Distributor ID: Ubuntu Description: Ubuntu 16.04.7 LTS Release: 16.04 Codename: xenial ``` `vscode version`: ``` version: 1.51.1 ``` `Remote - SSH ms-vscode-remote.remote-ssh`: ``` v0.61.0 ```
